			<Group Name="Ogre Big Names">
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Mawseeker</Name>
					<Points>40</Points>
					<AddToToughness>1</AddToToughness>
					<Stupidity/>
					<Description>A Tyrant with the Mawseeker name has +1 Toughness on his profile. He also suffers from the Stupidity special rule.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Wallcrusher</Name>
					<Points>30</Points>
					<ImpactHit>2</ImpactHit>
					<Description>Wallcrushers do one additional Impact Hit on a successful Ogre Charge. In addition, Wallcrushers ignore all the effects of obstacles when attacking units that are defending them -he is likely to barge through or smash it down on top of the foe. This does not benefit a unit he joins.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Kineater</Name>
					<Points>25</Points>
					<Rule>Any friendly unit within 6" may re-roll failed Panic tests</Rule>
					<Description>Any friendly unit within 6" of a Kineater may re-roll failed Panic tests.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Mountaineater</Name>
					<Points>25</Points>
					<Rule>Never be wounded on a score better than a 3+</Rule>
					<Rule>Hits that cause automatic Wounds are unaffected</Rule>
					<Description>A Mountaineater will never be wounded on a score better than a 3+. For instance, if the Mountaineater was hit by a cannonball (normally wounding him on the roll of a 2+) the cannonball would only wound him on a 3+ . Hits that cause automatic Wounds are unaffected.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Giantbreaker</Name>
					<Points>25</Points>
					<AddToStrength>1</AddToStrength>
					<Rule>May never refuse challenges, and neither he nor a unit he is with may choose to flee as a charge reaction</Rule>
					<Description>A character with the Giantbreaker name has +1 Strength on his profile. He may never refuse challenges, and neither he nor a unit he is with may choose to flee as a charge reaction.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Deathcheater</Name>
					<Points>20</Points>
					<AddToStrength>1</AddToStrength>
					<Rule>Once per game, nominate one model in base contact that has hit the Deathcheater but not yet rolled To Wound: that model must re-roll all successful To Wound rolls this phase</Rule>
					<Description>Once per game, nominate one model in base contact that has hit the Deathcheater but not yet rolled To Wound. That model must re-roll all successful To Wound rolls this phase. This includes all rolls To Wound made by the model's mount, chariot or other extra attacks.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Longstrider</Name>
					<Points>20</Points>
					<AddToMovement>1</AddToMovement>
					<Description>A character with the Longstrider big name has + 1 Movement on his profile.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Beastkiller</Name>
					<Points>20</Points>
					<Rule>Any attacks against a Large Target gains +1 on his rolls To Wound</Rule>
					<Description>When making attacks against a Large Target (either close combat or shooting), the Beastkiller gains +1 on his rolls To Wound — the Hunter knows just where to strike his prey for maximum effect. If the character is using a magic weapon, then he does not get this bonus.</Description>
				</Weapon>
				<Weapon>
					<Name>Brawlerguts</Name>
					<Points>15</Points>
					<Rule>Re-roll failed To Wound rolls from Impact Hits</Rule>
					<Description>Brawlerguts (but not their mounts) re-roll failed To Wound rolls from their Impact Hits.</Description>
				</Weapon>
